Title: Queen Of The Nile

reviewText: Edmund Purdom once again is the center of royal intrigue in the New Kingdom of ancient Egypt at the time of the Pharaoh Akhnaton, who keeps his original name in this version of his story, Amenophis IV. The plot of the film involves the making of the beautiful bust of Akhnaton's queen Nefertiti. Purdom plays the sculptor Tumos, who sculps the bust. Vincent Price is the evil high priest. This film would appeal to epic lovers like myself, who love to travel back via film to far away times and places. This film is partially dubbed in English, but there are notable American performers in it, which is a plus: Vincent Price, Edmund Purdom, and the star Jeanne Crain as Thanet-Nefertiti.If you have a collection of epic films from the 50s and 60s, you'll like this one.
Title: Queen Of The Nile

reviewText: Jeanne Crain is always perfect in any role she is in. This movie is a "Keeper" for sure!A great choice for children to learn their History.
